page.title: 16My Day (3)
page.content: A day in my life My name is Tracey Underwood I am 10 years old.I live at 20 Bridge Street,Richmond.I rise at 7.30am get dressed washed and clean my teeth and have breakfast put my coat and set off for Richmond Methodist where my friend Alison is waiting.We go in at 8.55am.Mr.Bland our head master takes Assembly we then do maths with Mr.Ackroyd.After break we have English write stories or work from books.At 12.00 I have a packed lunch.In the afternoon we do Art Computer work or Environment until 2.20pm.After afternoon break we Read or have P.E.At 3.35pm I walk home with Claire and Louise.I arrive home at 4.15pm I feed Tiddles my cat and my four goldfish.Then I go roller skating or watch t.v.At 9.30 I go to bed.
